=begin

Write a regex that matches the word `"cat"` when it occurs
at the end of a line.

Test strings:
  "The lazy cat sleeps
  The number 623 is not a cat
  The Alaskan drives a snowcat"

=end

str = "The lazy cat sleeps
The number 623 is not a cat
The Alaskan drives a snowcat"

pattern = /\bcat$/

matches = str.scan(pattern)

p matches
p matches.count
